The body of a woman who fell to her death while meditating at a popular lookout in the NSW Blue Mountains has been found in a tree 40 metres below.

Police are trying recover the body of the 22-year-old woman who fell from a cliff at Evans Lookout, near Blackheath.

The woman, who hails from Victoria, was with friends when she climbed over a railing near the edge of the cliff at about 9pm on Monday night.

